longBusinessSummary: Industries Qatar Q.P.S.C., through its subsidiaries operates petrochemical, fertilizer, and steel businesses in Qatar. Its Petrochemicals segment engages in the production and sale of ethylene, low density and linear low density polyethylene, methanol, caustic soda, ethylene dichloride, vinyl chloride monomer, Sulphur, pyrolysis gasoline, and mixed liquid petroleum gas, C3/C4 products. The Fertilizers segment produces and sells urea, ammonia, melamine, and urea formaldehyde condensate. Its Steel segment engages in production and sale of intermediary steel products, such as direct reduced and hot-briquetted iron, and steel billets; and final steel products including rebar and coil. The company also exports its products. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Doha, Qatar. Industries Qatar Q.P.S.C. operates as a subsidiary of QatarEnergy.
